RACE.RACE_TEXT: ELLIS PARK RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Maiden Claiming Purse 25000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five and One Hal f furlongs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MENDED WE STAND set the pace in the two path, kicked away from an outer presser entering upper stretch and held sway. RATIFIED tracked in the four path, gained between horses approaching the three furlong pole to gain show soon after, tipped inwardly behind the top pair entering the lane, gained place from an outer rival at the furlong grounds and chased the winner home. MRS. SPEAKER laid off of the pace two wide, shifted out to the five path in upper stretch and stayed on. MIDNIGHT XO chased along the inside, shifted outwardly nearing midstretch but lacked a punch. GET BY pressed outside of the winner while in the three path around the turn, but yielded in the four path entering the lane and weakened. MIDNIGHT SONATA broke outwardly while off slow, trailed along the inside and failed to factor. ELEGANT MOVES chased from midpack in the four path, but drifted out to the six path around the bend before weakening turning for home.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: REGAL RUMOR broke sharp and outwardly towards open space, vied with an inner rival into and around the turn, wrestled an advantage leaving the quarter pole and drove clear through the final furlong with good energy. MAKEUP vied for the lead inside of the eventual winner, but got headed by that one passing the quarter pole, proved no match in midstretch and remained clear of show. HIGH SHOT chased the embattled leading pair from the three path around the turn, failed to keep pace with those two entering the lane and held show from an inner bidder through the final furlong. LOOKSTER tracked in the two path, bid for show inside of a rival entering the final furlong but was kept at bay. NOVARA lacked speed in the four path and faded. BABE IN THE WOODS laid off of the pace along the inside and failed to factor. GRAND PRAIRIE GAL broke a step slow, trailed two wide and got outrun.

SUPREMELY was restless in the starting gate, tracked two wide and between horses around the turn, ran on to attempt a bid for place in the final furlong, but was kept at bay while getting outfinished for show at the wire. CAPTAIN JACK chased along the inside and lacked a bid. BOLT ABOVE broke outwardly, pursued from off of the pace in the four path, but drifted out at the furlong grounds and faded. RACE.RACE_TEXT: ELLIS PARK RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 73. Maiden Special Weight Purse 70000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 119 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PEIGNOIR set the pace, built a clear margin approaching the far turn, showed the way in the two path around that bend, then drew off under a busy ride in upper stretch and was kept to task thereafter. PROMISEMEANEMPIRE tracked two wide and between horses, awaited racing room behind rivals around the far turn, tipped inwardly nearing the lane, surged inside of rivals to gain place passing the three sixteenths pole and was clearly second best. AUDIOBOOK leaned out and snagged the outer half of the starting gate, then was taken in hand while shying from an inner rival early on, tracked along the inside, vied for place with outer foes around the far turn, gained that position while shifting off the rail nearing the lane, but was outkicked by an inner rival entering it and was best of the rest. CARARRA prompted the pace two wide and between horses entering the backstretch, but chased the clear leader from among foes around the far turn and yielded after being floated to the four path nearing the lane. SINGSATIONAL stalked three wide, lacked a bid despite urging around the far turn and faded after being fanned to the five path nearing the lane. PULA lacked speed in the four path and was done early.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ELLIS PARK RACE 6 1M Dirt CR: 75. Maiden Claiming Purse 25000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One mile out of the chute.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KEEN CONTENDER was slow into stride and trailed early on, improved in the three path around the far turn, launched a rally while splitting foes four wide in upper stretch, steadily closed in on the tiring leader in the final sixteenth and drove past that one in the shadow of the wire. SHE'S MAGIC settled off of the pace in the two path, took closer order inside of rivals at the five furlong pole, chased while vying for show around the far turn, tipped out in upper stretch and rallied along with an outer rival through the final furlong, but was outkicked by that one late and narrowly gained place. RED JAG set the pace in the two path, met an outer challenge around the far turn, repelled that rival and shook free entering the lane, maintained a clear margin through midstretch, but tired entering the final furlong, was caught approaching the wire and got nailed for place. INSIGHTFUL MISS pressed the leader from the three path, bid around the far turn, but was turned away entering the lane and gave way. BIRDIE ROSE tracked in the three path, then between horses moving down the backstretch, chased the top pair while vying for show with an inner rival around the far turn, but faded once floated five wide in upper stretch. KING'S MISTRESS stalked outside of the top pair and from the four path, but weakened in the five path entering the far turn. STORM HAVEN lacked speed in the five to four path and faded.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ELLIS PARK RACE 7 1M Dirt CR: 87. Maiden Special Weight Purse 70000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For $30,000 Or Less In Last 5 Starts).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HIGHLAND FALLS trailed along the inside early on, picked up stride in the four path around the far turn, fanned to the six path nearing the lane, yet sustained his charge to range up to the clear leader with a sixteenth to go and edged past late. MO FIGHT pursued from midpack in the four to five path, quickly gained around the far turn to boldly blow past the leaders at the five sixteenths pole, drew clear at the quarter pole, held sway through midstretch, but met an outer challenge in the final sixteenth and was bested. RIVALRY laid close up along the inside, but was shuffled back behind the faltering pace setter at the three furlong pole, maneuvered outside of that one as an outer rival rallied alongside turning for home, shifted to the five path while between horses in upper stretch, but drifted inwardly while changing to his right lead at the furlong grounds and only managed to chase thereafter. LUNA VIEJA laid off of the pace two wide, but was urged along in the three path and between horses around the far turn and failed to factor. DISSOLVED stalked in the four path, bid along with an outer rival at the five sixteenths pole, but was outkicked by that one soon after and weakened through the final furlong. FEAR OF UNION lacked speed along the inside, but failed to respond to urging around the far turn. PROVISIONAL set the pace in the three to two path, but was overhauled by a pair of outer bidders at the five sixteenths pole and caved. ABSOLUTELY CERTAIN broke a step slow and got outrun in the four path.

PAT'SCHROMECOMPASS tracked two wide, but was urged along in the three path while between horses around the turn and faded.
